## Summary
- Replace `base64-simd` crate with V8's bundled simdutf library (exposed via `v8::simdutf`) for all base64 encode/decode operations
- Update `v8` crate to 146.9.0 and enable the `simdutf` feature
- Remove `base64-simd` dependency from `ext/web`
- Use `v8::String::new_external_onebyte` for large base64 encode output (>8KB) to avoid copying into V8's heap, matching Node.js's approach
- Use `MaybeUninit` / `Vec::with_capacity` to avoid unnecessary zeroing of buffers before simdutf writes
- Call base64 ops directly from `buffer.mjs` instead of going through JS wrapper functions
- Avoids potential C++ symbol clashes when linking separate simdutf alongside V8

