`emitAfter` and `setAsyncContext` are outside the finally block. If `emitDestroy` throws (which it shouldn't, but still), these won't run. The old code in `_next_tick.ts` had both `emitAfter` and `setAsyncContext` inside the finally. Probably intentional to match Node's ordering but worth double checking.

